----------------------------------------------------

VIRA-AI MODULAR BACKEND - DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONMENT SETTINGS

----------------------------------------------------

--- 1. GENERAL APPLICATION SETTINGS ---

Set the current environment for the application (dev, staging, prod)

APP_ENV="development"

Port for Uvicorn server in local development

PORT=8000

SECRET KEY: MUST be a long, random, and unique string.

Used for session security, token signing, etc.

SECRET_KEY="your_very_secure_development_secret_key_change_me"

--- 2. DATABASE CONFIGURATION (PostgreSQL Example) ---

Replace with your actual database credentials and host for local testing.

DB_HOST="localhost"
DB_PORT="5432"
DB_NAME="viraai_db"
DB_USER="viraai_user"
DB_PASSWORD="viraai_password"

SQLAlchemy URL for connecting to the database

Example format: postgresql+psycopg2://user:password@host:port/dbname

DATABASE_URL="postgresql+psycopg2://${DB_USER}:${DB_PASSWORD}@${DB_HOST}:${DB_PORT}/${DB_NAME}"

--- 3. SECURITY & AUTHENTICATION (JWT) ---

Algorithm used for signing JWT tokens (e.g., HS256)

JWT_ALGORITHM="HS256"

Lifetime of the access token in minutes

ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=30

Lifetime of the refresh token in days

REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS=7

--- 4. THIRD-PARTY API KEYS (Examples) ---

Place actual API keys here for external services

OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."

HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY="..."

--- 5. LOGGING SETTINGS ---

Set logging level (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR)

LOG_LEVEL="DEBUG"
